    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix type mismatch in AT command response format variables\n\n### Summary\nThe AT command parser in the NAS stack had type mismatches between extern declarations and actual variable definitions. The variables `at_response_format_v1` and `at_error_code_suppression_q1` were declared as `int` in extern declarations but defined as `bool` in their implementation files. This inconsistency could lead to undefined behavior when these variables are accessed, particularly in the `parse_v1()` and `parse_v0()` functions which set these variables to boolean values.\n\nThis fix ensures consistent typing by updating the extern declarations to match the actual boolean definitions, and includes the necessary `stdbool.h` header for proper boolean type support.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_command.c`: Updated extern declarations from `int` to `bool` for `at_response_format_v1` and `at_error_code_suppression_q1`, and added `stdbool.h` include.\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_error.c`: Updated extern declaration from `int` to `bool` for `at_response_format_v1`.\n\n"
}